The paper discusses the structure of data-sharing relationships in large-scale data distribution systems, which involves analyzing network structures and patterns. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.NI (networking and internet architecture), cs.SOC (computational social science), and cs.DB (databases). Among these, cs.SI and cs.DS are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the analysis of network structures and patterns. cs.NI is also likely, as the paper discusses data distribution systems and their mechanisms. cs.SOC and cs.DB are less likely, but still possible, as the paper touches on social and computational aspects of data sharing, as well as database design considerations.
